          "Doubling time $\\approx 70/2 = 35$ years"
        ],
        "final_answer": "35 years"
      },
      "key_concepts": [
        "Doubling time",
        "Rule of 70",
        "Population growth"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "W2-Q11",
      "type": "multi_part",
      "topic": "Compound interest",
      "exam_alignment": "Geometric series application",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "question": "An investment of $10,000 earns 6% annual interest, compounded annually.",
      "parts": [
        {
          "part": "a",
          "question": "Write the value $V(n)$ after $n$ years as a geometric sequence formula.",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "First term $a = 10000$",
              "Common ratio $r = 1.06$",
              "$V(n) = 10000 \\times (1.06)^n$"
            ],
            "answer": "$V(n) = 10000(1.06)^n$"
          }
        },
        {
          "part": "b",
          "question": "What is the value after 10 years?",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "$V(10) = 10000 \\times (1.06)^{10}$",
              "$= 10000 \\times 1.7908 = \\$17{,}908.48$"
            ],
            "answer": "\\$17,908.48"
          }
        },
        {
          "part": "c",
          "question": "How many years until the investment triples?",
          "solution": {
            "steps": [
              "Need: $10000(1.06)^n = 30000$",
              "$(1.06)^n = 3$",
              "$n \\times \\ln(1.06) = \\ln(3)$",
              "$n = \\ln(3)/\\ln(1.06) = 1.099/0.0583 = 18.85$ years"
            ],
            "answer": "$\\approx 19$ years"
          }
        }
      ],
      "key_concepts": [
        "Compound interest",
        "Geometric growth",
        "Solving exponential equations"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "W2-Q12",
      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "topic": "Graph identification",
      "exam_alignment": "Q11 style",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "question": "A population $P$ grows exponentially: $P(t) = 2e^{0.1t}$. Which property must the graph have?",
      "options": {
        "a": "Passes through $(0, 2)$ and is always increasing",
        "b": "Passes through $(0, 1)$ and has horizontal asymptote at $y = 2$",
        "c": "Passes through $(0, 2)$ and approaches zero as $t \\to \\infty$",
        "d": "Is a straight line with slope $0.1$",
        "e": "None of the above"
      },
      "correct_answer": "a",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "At $t=0$: $P(0) = 2e^0 = 2 \\times 1 = 2$, so passes through $(0,2)$",
          "Since exponent $0.1t > 0$ when $t > 0$, function is increasing",
          "As $t \\to \\infty$, $P(t) \\to \\infty$ (exponential growth)",
          "No horizontal asymptote for large $t$"
        ],
        "final_answer": "Passes through (0, 2) and is always increasing"
      },
      "key_concepts": [
        "Exponential graphs",
        "Initial conditions",
        "Growth behaviour"
      ]
    }
  ]
